BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Campfire Storytime\, Brown County State Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260501T193000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260501T201500
UID:2fe69aa5c6472e6aa608ab1de5344c33@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:Join the nature center mascots\, Olive the Owl and Doug the De
 er\, and a park naturalist for a story reading. We will read Mossy &nbsp\;
 by Jan Brett&nbsp\;and enjoy a small campfire at the edge of the woods. Me
 et at the fire ring behind the Friends&#39\; Shelterhouse near the Nature 
 Center. Come early to enjoy the fire if you like! We will take suggestions
  on kid friendly books about nature! Feel free to suggest a favorite of yo
 urs to the naturalist! Owl Moon \, The Lorax \, Mossy \, and Zee Grows A T
 ree are popular titles\, but we&#39\;d love to add more variety!
LOCATION:Brown County State Park\, Nature Center (Friends' Circle)\, 1405 
 S.R. 46 W\, Nashville\, IN 
URL:https://on.in.gov/browncountysp
X-SOURCE:Brown County State Park
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Full Moon Hike\, Brown County State Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260501T210000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260501T223000
UID:92b0bbf60d6ace1630d6114ea7a55cbd@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:Join a park naturalist for a guided night hike around Lake Ogl
 e! The Full Moon is the brightest night of the month\, leading to excellen
 t views of the lake. Learn about May&#39\;s full moon\, the Flower Moon. T
 rail 7 is rated moderate\, but should be considered rugged in the dark. Th
 e trail has some staircases\, uneven surfaces\, and muddy spots. It is 1.2
  miles and will take about an hour and a half to complete. Please do not b
 ring pets on night hikes. Red flashlights are preferred for night vision a
 nd can be loaned to hikers on request.
LOCATION:Brown County State Park\, Lake Ogle parking lot\, 1405 S.R. 46 W\
 , Nashville\, IN 
URL:https://on.in.gov/BrownCountySP
X-SOURCE:Brown County State Park
END:VEVENT
BEGIN:VEVENT
SUMMARY:Mammal Furs\, Brown County State Park
DTSTART;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260502T110000
DTEND;TZID=America/Indiana/Indianapolis:20260502T113000
UID:04d56cb355f0598c51ce972cc20a6f1f@events.in.gov
DESCRIPTION:Did you know that not all fur is the same? Different animals u
 se their fur for camoflauge\, protection\, and keeping warm in a variety o
 f habitats. Visit the Nature Center to learn about Indiana&#39\;s native m
 ammals. Learn about their habits\, habitats\, play a short game\, and touc
 h real animal furs!
LOCATION:Brown County State Park\, Nature Center\, 1405 S.R. 46 W\, Nashvi
 lle\, IN 
URL:https://on.in.gov/browncountysp
X-SOURCE:Brown County State Park
END:VEVENT
